{"word":"διακονέω","slug":"διακονέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>διακονέω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:διάκονος'><el>διάκονος</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to minister, serve, do service</i>, <a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>; <el>τινι</el> to a person, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b>; <el>δ. πρός τι</el> <i>to be serviceable</i> towards, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>:—<a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a> <i>to minister to one's own needs</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>; <el>αὑτῶι διακονεῖσθαι</el> <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>to be a deacon</i>, <b><a href='S:New Testament'>NTest.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> rei, <i>to furnish, supply</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>ministrare</el>, <el>τί τινι</el> <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to be supplied</i>, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}